<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1290,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1290,1315]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Integument brown. Body with pubescence whitish. Elytra with two dark-brown spots, one in anterior region and the other postmedian and with longitudinal brown bands laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1290,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
Upper eye lobes well separated, distance between them equal to almost three times the width of a lobe. Antennae exceeding elytral apices at antennomere VI. Scape subequal in length to antennomere III; III–VIII subequal in length, IX–XI gradually increasing in length, XI 
<number box="[857,892,1434,1458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times the length of antennomere III. Pronotum uniformly and deeply punctate. Lateral tubercle with base and surrounding area dilated. Prosternal process 
<number box="[1369,1379,1470,1494]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1390,1405,1470,1494]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
as wide as procoxal cavity. Mesosternum depressed. Mesosternal process 
<number box="[949,959,1506,1530]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[969,984,1506,1530]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
as wide as mesocoxal cavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1290,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Elytra approximately three times as long as prothorax, surface finely punctate, denser anteriorly. Humeri slightly projected anteriorly. Apices obliquely truncate, angles slightly produced.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1290,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
Metatarsomere I 
<number box="[404,439,1614,1638]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as II–III together. Apex of urotergite V emarginate; urosternite V semicircular with angles strongly produced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1290,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Female. Apex of urotergite V acute and gradually narrowed distally; urosternite V emarginate, exceeding the elytral apices by more than half its length.</paragraph>
