<taxonomicNameLabel box="[984,1112,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1105,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
It is distinguished by having the female urosternite V exceeding the elytral apices by more than half of its length. 
<taxonomicName box="[1137,1436,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eucharitolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorcadioides" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1137,1436,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Eucharitolus dorcadioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[153,281,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[153,281,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a shorter urosternite V which does not exceed the elytral apices by more than half its length.
</paragraph>
